        "text": "Unity Software (\"Unity\") welcomes the opportunity to contribute to the European Commission's call for evidence on the proposed Digital Fairness Act (DFA). Unity is a global leading platform with $45\\%$ of its workforce based in Europe that helps developers create and grow interactive content and experiences across industries - from gaming and automotive to retail and education. Our real-time 3D (RT3D) technology enables them to build, optimize, and scale content across more than 20 platforms, including mobile, PC, console, and extended reality (XR). Developers retain autonomy over how and where they reach audiences, aligning with the EU's emphasis on platform neutrality and user choice.",
